The paper deals with probabilistic logic programs, which are a combination of logic programming and probabilistic reasoning. This makes it likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses inference and learning tasks, which are common in Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) and Database (cs.DB) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes algorithms for parameter estimation, which is a topic in Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
